4
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:09,690
I have always been fascinated by biology.

5
00:00:09,690 --> 00:00:13,080
What excites me the most is
really the ability to see

6
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:16,350
how molecules move around and interact.

7
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:17,730
My research group focuses

8
00:00:17,730 --> 00:00:20,490
on developing new photostable probe

9
00:00:20,490 --> 00:00:23,760
that allows us to do long-term
single-molecule tracking

10
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:25,050
inside living systems.

11
00:00:25,050 --> 00:00:27,240
We know that diseases are often caused

12
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:29,310
by mutations in certain proteins,

13
00:00:29,310 --> 00:00:32,820
and so now if we can really
visualize the differences

14
00:00:32,820 --> 00:00:34,440
of the molecular dynamics,

15
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:37,170
we can potentially screen
for small molecules

16
00:00:37,170 --> 00:00:39,810
that can help revert
this kind of behavior.

17
00:00:39,810 --> 00:00:43,710
This will be very useful
information to guide our design

18
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:45,933
of the next generation of therapeutics.

19
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:49,680
Because this is a
relatively new technology,

20
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:52,560
we need to optimize many different fields.

21
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:55,290
I'm really fortunate to be
able to recruit our students

22
00:00:55,290 --> 00:00:57,090
with very different skills.

23
00:00:57,090 --> 00:00:58,800
Students who can synthesize

24
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,690
and optimize these nanoparticles.

25
00:01:00,690 --> 00:01:02,940
We also have students
who are good at optics

26
00:01:02,940 --> 00:01:04,740
and can build the microscopes.

27
00:01:04,740 --> 00:01:06,690
And so these students are really talented

28
00:01:06,690 --> 00:01:08,190
and they're really driven

29
00:01:08,190 --> 00:01:11,468
to really push the frontier
of our scientific research.

30
